  "datePublished": "2026-03-05",
  "description": "A haiku is a short Japanese poetic form traditionally composed in three phrases of 5, 7, and 5 *on* (sound units roughly analogous to syllables). In English, the form is conventionally rendered as three lines, though the syllable count is debated — Japanese *on* are shorter than English syllables, and many English-language haiku poets prefer brevity over strict 5-7-5 adherence.",
